374enum eGpsStatus
375{
376 GPS_STATUS_NUM_SATS_USED_MASK = (int)0x000000FF,
377
379 GPS_STATUS_FIX_NONE = (int)0x00000000,
380 GPS_STATUS_FIX_DEAD_RECKONING_ONLY = (int)0x00000100,
381 GPS_STATUS_FIX_2D = (int)0x00000200,
382 GPS_STATUS_FIX_3D = (int)0x00000300,
383 GPS_STATUS_FIX_GPS_PLUS_DEAD_RECK = (int)0x00000400,
384 GPS_STATUS_FIX_TIME_ONLY = (int)0x00000500,
385 GPS_STATUS_FIX_UNUSED1 = (int)0x00000600,
386 GPS_STATUS_FIX_UNUSED2 = (int)0x00000700,
387 GPS_STATUS_FIX_DGPS = (int)0x00000800,
388 GPS_STATUS_FIX_SBAS = (int)0x00000900,
389 GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_SINGLE = (int)0x00000A00,
390 GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_FLOAT = (int)0x00000B00,
391 GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_FIX = (int)0x00000C00,
392 GPS_STATUS_FIX_MASK = (int)0x00001F00,
393 GPS_STATUS_FIX_BIT_OFFSET = (int)8,
394
396 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_FIX_OK = (int)0x00010000, // within limits (e.g. DOP & accuracy)
397 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_DGPS_USED = (int)0x00020000, // Differential GPS (DGPS) used.
398 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_FIX_AND_HOLD = (int)0x00040000, // RTK feedback on the integer solutions to drive the float biases towards the resolved integers
399// GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_WEEK_VALID = (int)0x00040000,
400// GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_TOW_VALID = (int)0x00080000,
401 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_POSITION_ENABLED = (int)0x00100000, // RTK precision positioning mode enabled
402 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_STATIC_MODE = (int)0x00200000, // Static mode
403 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_ENABLED = (int)0x00400000, // RTK moving base mode enabled
404 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_RAW_GPS_DATA_ERROR = (int)0x00800000, // RTK error: observations or ephemeris are invalid or not received (i.e. RTK differential corrections)
405 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_DATA_MISSING = (int)0x01000000, // RTK error: Either base observations or antenna position have not been received.
406 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_MOVING = (int)0x02000000, // RTK error: base position moved when it should be stationary
407 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_INVALID = (int)0x03000000, // RTK error: base position is invalid or not surveyed well
408 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_MASK = (int)0x03000000, // RTK error: base position error bitmask
409 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_ERROR_MASK = (GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_RAW_GPS_DATA_ERROR|
410 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_MASK),
411 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_POSITION_VALID = (int)0x04000000, // GPS1 RTK precision position and carrier phase range solution with fixed ambiguities (i.e. < 6cm horizontal accuracy). The carrier phase range solution with floating ambiguities occurs if GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_FIX is set and GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_POSITION_VALID is not set (i.e. > 6cm horizontal accuracy).
412 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_VALID = (int)0x08000000, // GPS2 RTK moving base heading. Indicates RTK fix and hold with single band RTK compassing.
413 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_BAD = (int)0x00002000,
414 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_UNSET = (int)0x00004000,
415 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_MASK = (GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_ENABLED|
416 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_VALID|
417 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_BAD|
418 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_UNSET),
419 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_GPS_NMEA_DATA = (int)0x00008000, // 1 = Data from NMEA message
420 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_MASK = (int)0x0FFFE000,
421 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_BIT_OFFSET = (int)16,

1683 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_ZERO_ACCEL = 3, // Zero only accel biases.

1688 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_OPTION_DISABLE_MOTION_DETECT = 0x00010000, // Bitwise AND this with the above init commands to disable motion detection during sampling (allow for more tolerant sampling).
1689 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_OPTION_DISABLE_REQUIRE_VERTIAL = 0x00020000, // Bitwise AND this with the above init commands to disable vertical alignment requirement for accelerometer bias calibration (allow for more tolerant sampling).
1690
1692 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_START_SAMPLE = 8, // Initiate 5 second sensor sampling and averaging. Run for each orientation and 180 degree yaw rotation.
1693 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_SAVE_AND_FINISH = 9, // Run this command to compute and save results. Must be run following INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_START_SAMPLE.
1694
1696 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_READY_FOR_SAMPLING = 50, // System has been initialized and is waiting for user to intiate sampling. User must send a command to exit this state.
1697 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_SAMPLING = 51, // System is averaging the IMU data. Minimize all motion and vibration.
1698 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_RUN_BIT_AND_FINISH = 52, // Follow up calibration zero with BIT and copy out IMU biases.
1699 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_SAVED_AND_FINISHED = 53, // Calculations are complete and DID_INFIELD_CAL.imu holds the update IMU biases. Updates are saved to flash.
1700
1702 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_NOT_INITIALIZED = 100, // Init command (INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_...) not set.
1703 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_SAMPLE_ABORT_MOTION_DETECTED= 101, // Error: Motion detected. Sampling aborted.
1704 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_SAMPLE_ABORT_NOT_VERTICAL = 102, // Error: System not vertical. Sampling aborted.
1705 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_NO_SAMPLES_COLLECTED = 103, // Error: No samples have been collected
1706 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_POOR_CAL_FIT = 104, // Error: Calibration zero is not
1707
1709 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_MASK = 0x0000FFFF,
1710 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_START_SAMPLE_BIT = 11, // Initiate 5 second sensor sample and averaging. Does not save sample into cal data.
1711};

4064// BE_SWAP: if big endian then swap, else no-op
4065// LE_SWAP: if little endian then swap, else no-op
4066#if CPU_IS_BIG_ENDIAN
4067#define BE_SWAP64F(_i) flipDoubleCopy(_i)
4068#define BE_SWAP32F(_i) flipFloatCopy(_i)
4069#define BE_SWAP32(_i) (SWAP32(_i))
4070#define BE_SWAP16(_i) (SWAP16(_i))
4071#define LE_SWAP64F(_i) (_i)
4072#define LE_SWAP32F(_i) (_i)
4073#define LE_SWAP32(_i) (_i)
4074#define LE_SWAP16(_i) (_i)
4075#else // little endian
4076#define BE_SWAP64F(_i) (_i)
4077#define BE_SWAP32F(_i) (_i)
4078#define BE_SWAP32(_i) (_i)
4079#define BE_SWAP16(_i) (_i)
4080#define LE_SWAP64F(_i) flipDoubleCopy(_i)
4081#define LE_SWAP32F(_i) flipFloatCopy(_i)
4082#define LE_SWAP32(_i) (SWAP32(_i))
4083#define LE_SWAP16(_i) (SWAP16(_i))
4084#endif
